                        SQUADRON OF DISTINCTION 2000

                 Group 7 Composite Squadron of the Year 2000

                      California Wing Color Guard 2001

        The Civil Air Patrol provides one of the most fun, exciting,
    challenging and rewarding programs available for young people today.


     Some things you will learn:
   Military customs & courtesies
        Map reading & navigation
             Aerospace Education
             Survival techniques
               Leadership skills
                        Teamwork

                                Some things you can do:
                                Orientation flights
                                Overnight bivouacs
                                Color Guard competition
                                Tour military installations
                                Search for missing aircraft
                                Build and fly model rockets
                                National Activities

   Thanks to all of the visitors and members who made our Open House a
   great success.   And  a special thanks to General Bolden for sharing
   his experiences as a Marine Corps. pilot and Space Shuttle commander.

     Anyone interested in finding out more about the Civil Air Patrol is
   always welcome to come and visit us on any Tuesday night from 6:45pm to
   9:15pm.
   (There will be no meetings on Christmas or New Year's Day)
   Squadron 47 Meeting Schedule
   Directions to Squadron 47
   If you have any questions about CAP or Squadron 47 call (760) 943-7780
